cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a wireless powered mobile edge computing network, which involves wireless devices and transmission time allocation. This is a clear indication that the paper belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimization of computation rate, which can be seen as an information theoretic problem. The use of wireless power transfer (WPT) also involves information theory concepts. Hence, cs.IT is a likely sub-category.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a joint optimization method based on the ADMM decomposition technique, which is a control theory method. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Systems and Control sub-category.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with distributed energy-harvesting wireless devices and binary computation offloading policy, which are related to distributed computing. Hence, cs.DC is a possible sub-category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves computation offloading and transmission time allocation, which are relevant to multimedia applications. Hence, cs.MM is a possible sub-category.
